{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Praise Yah! Praise Yahweh’s name!"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Praise him, you servants of Yahweh,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "you who st and in Yahweh’s house, in the courts of our God’s house."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Praise Yah, for Yahweh is good. Sing praises to his name, for that is pleasant."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For Yah has chosen Jacob for himself, Israel for his own possession."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I know that Yahweh is great, that our Lord is above all gods."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Whatever Yahweh pleased, that he has done, in heaven and in earth, in the seas and in all deeps."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He causes the clouds to rise from the ends of the earth. He makes lightnings with the rain."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He brings the wind out of his treasuries."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He struck the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and animal."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He sent signs and wonders into the middle of you, Egypt, on Pharaoh, and on all his servants."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He struck many nations, and killed mighty kings—"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Sihon king of the Amorites, Og king of Bashan,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and all the kingdoms of Canaan—"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and gave their land for a heritage, a heritage to Israel, his people."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Your name, Yahweh, endures forever; your renown, Yahweh, throughout all generations."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For Yahweh will judge his people and have compassion on his servants."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The idols of the nations are silver and gold, the work of men’s hands."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have mouths, but they can’t speak. They have eyes, but they can’t see."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have ears, but they can’t hear, neither is there any breath in their mouths."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Those who make them will be like them, yes, everyone who trusts in them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "House of Israel, praise Yahweh! House of Aaron, praise Yahweh!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "House of Levi, praise Yahweh! You who fear Yahweh, praise Yahweh!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Blessed be Yahweh from Zion, who dwells in Jerusalem. Praise Yah!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}